South Korea Beats India 3-2 in Davis Cup 
South Korea beat India 3-2 after drawing 1-1 in reverse singles matches
on Sunday in their Davis Cup Asia/Oceania zone Group One, first round
tie here:
Results (South Korean names first):
Lee Hyung-taik lost to Leander Paes 4-6, 4-6, 4-6
Yoon Yong-il beat Mahesh Bhupathi 6-7, 6-1, 6-1, 6-1
